data.问题: 这句话George真正想表达的含义是什么？

data.OPTION-B: George wants Angela to provide some travel advice
data.OPTION-C: George wants to say, "Can I drink something?" or "Can we rest a few minutes before we start talking about business?"
data.OPTION-D: George wants to complain to Angela about his trip

data.故事: 刘伟是一个身材魁梧的肌肉男，某天他第一次去岳父家，吃完了一碗米饭后，给大家讲了个故事：“前几天我到山里去，见到一只大老虎，那虎爪啊……”将空碗往桌上一倒扣，“有这么大！” 岳父立即想到是刘伟还没吃饱，就默默转身进厨房准备给他添饭。结果到了厨房一看，已经没有饭了。岳父略一思索就抱着锅出来，把空锅往桌上一倒扣：“那老虎头是不是有这么大？”

data.选项B: B. 岳父想提醒刘伟不要吹嘘自己的勇气
data.选项C: C. 岳父暗示锅中已经没有饭了
data.选项D: D. 岳父在揶揄刘伟的吃相
data.STORY: Liu Wei is a muscular man with a robust figure. One day, he goes to his father-in-law's house for the first time. After finishing a bowl of rice, he tells everyone a story: "A few days ago, I go to the mountain and see a big tiger, its claws..." He turns the empty bowl upside down on the table, "are this big!" The father-in-law immediately thinks that Liu Wei is still hungry, so he silently turns around and goes into the kitchen to get him more rice. But when he gets to the kitchen, there is no rice left. After a brief thought, the father-in-law comes out with the pot, turns the empty pot upside down on the table: "Is the tiger's head this big?"
data.QUESTION: What does the father-in-law really mean when he says this?
data.OPTION-A: The father-in-law hints that he once sees a big tiger
data.OPTION-B: The father-in-law wants to remind Liu Wei not to boast about his courage
data.OPTION-C: The father-in-law hints that there is no rice left in the pot
data.OPTION-D: The father-in-law is teasing Liu Wei's eating manners

data.故事: 19世纪，在奥地利的维也纳，妇女们喜欢戴一种高高耸起的帽子。她们进剧场看戏也不愿将帽子摘下，以致后排的观众被挡住了视线。经理上台请在座的女观众将帽子摘下来，然而说了半天妇女们也不予以理睬。最后经理又补充了一句：“那么，这样吧，年纪大一点的女士可以照顾，不必脱帽。”
data.问题: 剧场经理说这些话时，他真正想说的意思是什么？

data.选项B: B. 他只希望年纪轻的女士将帽子摘下来。
data.选项C: C. 他对戴帽子的女士感到恼火。
data.选项D: D. 他在夸赞年纪大的女士的优雅。
data.STORY: In the 19th century, in Vienna, Austria, women like to wear a kind of towering hat. They go to the theater to watch plays and do not want to take off their hats, so the audience in the back row is blocked. The manager goes on stage to ask the female audience to take off their hats, but the women ignore him after a long talk. Finally, the manager adds one more sentence: "So, like this, older ladies can take care, no need to take off the hat."
data.QUESTION: When the theater manager says these words, what does he really want to say?
data.OPTION-A: He hopes all ladies take off their hats.
data.OPTION-B: He only hopes young ladies take off their hats.
data.OPTION-C: He is annoyed with the ladies wearing hats.
data.OPTION-D: He is praising the elegance of older ladies.

data.故事: 小简高一的时候沉迷于小说，天天晚上躲在被窝里看，有时候上课也看，因此上课精神状态一直不太好。有一天出教室准备做广播操的时候，班主任走到小简旁边来说了一句：“小简，你最近是不是生病了？”
data.问题: 班主任说这些话时，她真正想说的意思是什么？
data.选项A: A. 班主任暗示小简应当好好上课，不要总是精神萎靡。
data.选项B: B. 班主任是在询问小简的健康状况。
data.选项C: C. 班主任让小简减少看小说的时间。
data.选项D: D. 班主任想让小简早点休息以保持健康。
data.STORY: When Xiao Jian is in the first year of high school, she is obsessed with novels, hiding in the quilt to read every night, and sometimes she reads during class, so her mental state in class is not very good. One day, when she is about to leave the classroom to do radio exercises, the head teacher comes to Xiao Jian and says, "Xiao Jian, are you sick recently?"
data.QUESTION: What does the head teacher really mean when she says these words?
data.OPTION-A: The head teacher implies that Xiao Jian should pay attention to class and not always be listless.
data.OPTION-B: The head teacher is inquiring about Xiao Jian's health.
data.OPTION-C: The head teacher wants Xiao Jian to reduce the time she spends reading novels.
data.OPTION-D: The head teacher wants Xiao Jian to rest early to maintain her health.

data.OPTION-D: The father implies that the son should get up.

鸿杰去银行帮朋友办事，朋友在外地，他找到工作人员要来了办事需要填写的表单，看到了签名那栏，愣住了，因为显示要本人签字。
他很耿直的问工作人员：“我朋友在外地，我可以代签吗？”
工作人员说：“这里有监控，是没法别人代签的，出去找本人签。”
他很着急的说：“我朋友真的回不来，行个方便吧。”
工作人员还是那句话：“这里有监控，别人没法代签，出去找本人签。”
data.问题: 当工作人员说这句话时，他真正想说的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 工作人员是在硬性要求鸿杰必须找他的朋友来银行签字。
data.选项B: B. 工作人员在暗示鸿杰可以走出银行后帮朋友代签。
data.选项C: C. 工作人员是再次确认了规定，即银行内不允许他人代签。
data.选项D: D. 工作人员是在建议鸿杰去找合适的签字工具。
data.STORY:
Hongjie goes to the bank to help a friend with some business. His friend is out of town. He gets the form that needs to be filled out from the staff and stops when he sees the signature column because it requires the person's own signature.
He asks the staff very straightforwardly: "My friend is out of town, can I sign for him?"
The staff says: "There is surveillance here, it is impossible for others to sign on behalf, go find the person to sign."
He says anxiously: "My friend really can't come back, please make it convenient."
The staff still says: "There is surveillance here, others can't sign on behalf, go find the person to sign."
data.QUESTION: What does the staff really mean when he says this?
data.OPTION-A: The staff is insisting that Hongjie must find his friend to come to the bank to sign.
data.OPTION-B: The staff is hinting that Hongjie can sign for his friend after leaving the bank.
data.OPTION-C: The staff is reconfirming the rule that the bank does not allow others to sign on behalf.
data.OPTION-D: The staff is suggesting that Hongjie find a suitable signing tool.

data.故事: 经理小张在公司开会的时候，发现他的同事小赵一直玩手机。他看了一眼小赵并说着：“我发现你一直在研究一些非常重要的东西啊。”
data.问题: 当小张说这句话时，他真正想说的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 小张表示他对小赵正在做的事情很感兴趣，希望也能得到其中的乐趣。
data.选项B: B. 小张暗示小赵开会时不应总看手机。
data.选项C: C. 小张表示他对小赵一直在手机上忙碌的情况表示理解。
data.选项D: D. 小张在赞美小赵能一边开会一边处理其他事情。
data.STORY: Manager Xiao Zhang, while in a company meeting, notices that his colleague Xiao Zhao constantly plays with his phone. He glances at Xiao Zhao and says, "I notice you are always studying some very important things."
data.QUESTION: What does Xiao Zhang really mean when he says this?
data.OPTION-A: Xiao Zhang shows his interest in what Xiao Zhao is doing and hopes to also get pleasure from it.
data.OPTION-B: Xiao Zhang implies that Xiao Zhao should not always look at his phone during meetings.
data.OPTION-C: Xiao Zhang shows his understanding of Xiao Zhao's constant busyness on the phone.
data.OPTION-D: Xiao Zhang praises Xiao Zhao for being able to handle other things while in a meeting.

output:

data.STORY: Yang Hua and Chen Bin are roommates. Yang Hua is a person who is extremely interested in computer knowledge and often tinkers with his own computer. One day, Chen Bin says to Yang Hua, "My computer starts to throw a tantrum again."
data.QUESTION: What does Chen Bin really want to say when he says this?
data.OPTION-A: He wants to express that his computer is working
data.OPTION-B: He hopes Yang Hua can help fix the computer problem

data.OPTION-D: He plans to buy a new computer to replace the existing one

data.故事: 小杨所在的公司周三有周例会。某周一，领导带着小王去会见客户张局，两人一直相谈甚欢，但谈的都是一些无关痛痒的话题，因为正事存在观点分歧。眼看着将近饭点，出现了下面几句对话： 领导：“张局，快到饭点了，看您有时间吗？想约您吃个饭？” 然后领导转过身，边眨眼睛，边对小杨说：“小杨，咱们晚上单位还有会议吗？”
data.问题: 当领导问小杨这个问题的时候，他的目的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 领导想向小杨询问会议时间，以安排和客户的饭局。
data.选项B: B. 领导希望小杨回答今晚有会议，以此借口结束会面。
data.选项C: C.领导想了解小杨对周例会的准备情况。
data.选项D: D. 领导希望询问小杨愿不愿不参加会议，而陪他们吃饭。
data.STORY: Xiao Yang's company holds a weekly meeting every Wednesday. On a certain Monday, the leader takes Xiao Wang to meet with client Director Zhang. The two of them chat happily, but they only talk about some irrelevant topics because there are disagreements on the main issues. As it approaches mealtime, the following conversation occurs: Leader: "Director Zhang, it is almost mealtime, do you have time? I want to invite you to have a meal." Then the leader turns around, winks, and says to Xiao Yang: "Xiao Yang, do we have a meeting at the unit tonight?"
data.QUESTION: What is the leader's purpose when he asks Xiao Yang this question?
data.OPTION-A: The leader wants to ask Xiao Yang about the meeting time to arrange a meal with the client.
data.OPTION-B: The leader hopes Xiao Yang answers that there is a meeting tonight, so he can use this as an excuse to end the meeting.
data.OPTION-C: The leader wants to understand Xiao Yang's preparation for the weekly meeting.
data.OPTION-D: The leader wants to ask if Xiao Yang is willing to skip the meeting and join them for dinner.

data.故事: 小汪和网络上认识的女生小兰的见面约在了酒店。在前台，小兰不愿意出示身份证登记。 前台工作人员问：“您是一位还是两位？两位的话需要出示双方身份证的先生。” 小汪回头看着小兰，她慢慢走到沙发边上坐下仍然没有出示身份证的意思。于是小汪转过头问：“两位，那怎么办？” 此时前台工作人员又问：“您是一位入住还是两位呢？”
data.问题: 当工作人员提出这个问题的时候，他的目的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 他没有听清楚小汪之前的回答，要再进行确认。
data.选项B: B. 他正在重新核实小汪的住宿需求。
data.选项C: C. 他暗示小汪可回答一位入住，这样只需要用一个人的身份证。
data.选项D: D. 他暗示不出示两人身份证就不可以一起住宿。
data.STORY: Xiao Wang and the girl he meets online, Xiao Lan, arrange to meet at a hotel. At the front desk, Xiao Lan does not want to show her ID for registration. The front desk staff asks, "Are you one or two? If two, the gentleman needs to show both IDs." Xiao Wang turns his head and looks at Xiao Lan, she slowly walks to the edge of the sofa and sits down, still showing no intention of showing her ID. So Xiao Wang turns his head and asks, "Two, what to do?" At this time, the front desk staff asks again, "Are you checking in for one or two?"
data.QUESTION: What is his purpose when the staff asks this question?
data.OPTION-A: He does not hear Xiao Wang's previous answer clearly and needs to confirm again.
data.OPTION-B: He is re-verifying Xiao Wang's accommodation needs.
data.OPTION-C: He hints that Xiao Wang can answer one person checks in, so only one person's ID is needed.
data.OPTION-D: He hints that if they do not show both IDs, they cannot stay together.

data.STORY: One day, Xiao Ming passes by a small alley, there is a small stall at the entrance of the alley that sells fried goods. Because Xiao Ming likes to eat melon seeds very much, he steps forward to buy two pounds. When buying, Xiao Ming gives the boss a hundred yuan bill, the boss takes the money, lowers his head and mutters a few words with the boss lady, and then hands out the previous bill, saying, "I can't make change, no small change." Xiao Ming feels a bit strange, but doesn't think much about it, takes the money and is about to walk away, Zhang San, who is passing by, says to himself, "Your melon seeds, they don't look like the real thing." After saying this, Zhang San walks away, and the boss just lowers his head and says nothing.
data.QUESTION: What does Zhang San really want to say when he says this?

data.故事: 明凯在大学爬泰山的时候买了个钥匙扣。他参加工作后，他的领导偶然看到这个钥匙扣，说“你这钥匙扣真漂亮啊，哪里买的？”明凯便把自己在泰山的经历绘声绘色说了一遍。过了几天，领导又看到明凯的钥匙扣，好像失忆了一样，又问“你这钥匙扣真漂亮啊，哪里买的？“
data.问题: 领导说这句话的时候，真正的意图是什么？
data.选项A: A. 领导对明凯的钥匙扣很感兴趣，考虑自己也去买一个。
data.选项B: B. 领导希望明凯能将这个钥匙扣送给他。
data.选项C: C. 领导想检验明凯的耐心，探究他是否愿意反复解释同一件事。
data.选项D: D. 领导提醒小明这个钥匙扣使他分心了
data.STORY: Mingkai buys a keychain when he climbs Mount Tai in college. After he starts working, his leader accidentally sees this keychain and says, "This keychain of yours is really beautiful, where do you buy it?" Mingkai then vividly tells his experience on Mount Tai. After a few days, the leader sees Mingkai's keychain again, as if he forgets, and asks again, "This keychain of yours is really beautiful, where do you buy it?"
data.QUESTION: What is the real intention of the leader when he says this?
data.OPTION-A: The leader is very interested in Mingkai's keychain and considers buying one for himself.
data.OPTION-B: The leader hopes that Mingkai gives this keychain to him.
data.OPTION-C: The leader wants to test Mingkai's patience, to explore whether he is willing to explain the same thing repeatedly.
data.OPTION-D: The leader reminds Mingkai that this keychain distracts him.

data.故事: 小红大概晚上9点到达火车站候车厅，进入后，她询问乘务员“这里可以待多久？”。乘务员回答：“最多三个小时，也就是到12点，你要不要现在就进去？”小红说：“可以的，我是凌晨3点的火车，我想着在这里休息到12点，出去再呆2个多小时。”此时，然后乘务员突然提醒说：“注意听广播提醒你上列车，不要误车。”
data.问题: 乘务员说这句话的时候，真正的意思是什么？
data.选项A: A. 乘务员在暗示小红可以在候车厅一直休息，直到上车。
data.选项B: B. 乘务员在告诫小红，夜晚出行安全问题需要提高警惕。
data.选项C: C. 乘务员在告诉小红，她必须在12点之前离开候车厅。
data.选项D: D. 乘务员在提醒小红要关注列车时刻表，以防错过火车。
data.STORY: Xiao Hong probably arrives at the train station waiting room at about 9 pm. After entering, she asks the conductor, "How long can I stay here?". The conductor replies, "Up to three hours, which is until 12 o'clock, do you want to go in now?" Xiao Hong says, "Yes, I am on the 3 am train, I think about resting here until 12 o'clock, then go out and stay for more than 2 hours." At this time, the conductor suddenly reminds, "Pay attention to the broadcast to remind you to get on the train, do not miss the train."
data.QUESTION: What is the real meaning when the conductor says this?
data.OPTION-A: The conductor implies that Xiao Hong can rest in the waiting room until she boards the train.
data.OPTION-B: The conductor warns Xiao Hong that she needs to be vigilant about safety issues when traveling at night.
data.OPTION-C: The conductor tells Xiao Hong that she must leave the waiting room before 12 o'clock.
data.OPTION-D: The conductor reminds Xiao Hong to pay attention to the train schedule to prevent missing the train.

data.故事: 刘伟是一个身材魁梧的肌肉男，某天他第一次去岳父家，吃完了一碗米饭后，给大家讲了个故事：“前几天我到山里去，见到一只大老虎，那虎爪啊……”将空碗往桌上一倒扣，“有这么大！” 岳父立即想到是刘伟还没吃饱，就默默转身进厨房准备给他添饭。结果到了厨房一看，已经没有饭了。岳父略一思索就抱着锅出来，把空锅往桌上一倒扣：“那老虎头是不是有这么大？”
data.问题: 岳父说这句话时，真正想说的意思是什么？
data.选项A: A. 岳父暗示他曾经亲见过一只大老虎
data.选项B: B. 岳父想提醒刘伟不要吹嘘自己的勇气
data.选项C: C. 岳父暗示锅中已经没有饭了
data.选项D: D. 岳父在揶揄刘伟的吃相
data.STORY: Liu Wei is a muscular man with a robust figure. One day, he goes to his father-in-law's house for the first time. After finishing a bowl of rice, he tells everyone a story: "A few days ago, I go to the mountain and see a big tiger, its claws..." He turns the empty bowl upside down on the table, "are this big!" The father-in-law immediately thinks that Liu Wei is still hungry, so he silently turns around and goes into the kitchen to get him more rice. But when he gets to the kitchen, there is no rice left. After a brief thought, the father-in-law comes out with the pot, turns the empty pot upside down on the table: "Is the tiger's head this big?"
data.QUESTION: What does the father-in-law really mean when he says this?
data.OPTION-A: The father-in-law hints that he once sees a big tiger
data.OPTION-B: The father-in-law wants to remind Liu Wei not to boast about his courage
data.OPTION-C: The father-in-law hints that there is no rice left in the pot
data.OPTION-D: The father-in-law is teasing Liu Wei's eating manners

data.故事:
以前周末的时候，老李总是把儿子小李送去妈妈家。后来小李渐渐就不去了，有一天妈妈给老李打了电话。
“儿子啊，我家里装了wifi，还买了一台新电脑，你帮我和孙子说声”
data.问题: 妈妈说这句话时，真正想说的意思是什么？
data.选项A: A. 妈妈希望老李多把小李带来家里。
data.选项B: B. 妈妈希望小李帮助她学习如何使用新电脑。
data.选项C: C. 妈妈希望和老李分享家里的新变化。
data.选项D: D. 妈妈希望小李能帮她测试新安装的wifi。
data.STORY: In the past, on weekends, Old Li always sends his son, Little Li, to his mother's house. Later, Little Li gradually stops going. One day, the mother calls Old Li.\n"Son, I install wifi at home and also buy a new computer, you tell my grandson for me."
data.QUESTION: What does the mother really mean when she says this?
data.OPTION-A: The mother hopes that Old Li brings Little Li to her house more often.
data.OPTION-B: The mother hopes that Little Li helps her learn how to use the new computer.
data.OPTION-C: The mother hopes to share the new changes at home with Old Li.
data.OPTION-D: The mother hopes that Little Li can help her test the newly installed wifi.

data.故事: 有次程伟带儿子逛商场，陪他去儿童游乐场玩，突然看到有个人牵着条狗进来，程伟就问这个人，“没看到这牌子上写着谢绝带宠物入场吗？”对方显得非常不屑，根本没打算理程伟。这个时候，一旁的儿子笑着和程伟说，“爸爸你真傻，狗又不认识字。”
data.问题: 当儿子说这句话时，他真正想说的意思是什么？
data.选项A: A. 儿子在讽刺这个人没有社会公德。

data.选项C: C. 儿子喜欢狗，希望拥有一只
data.选项D: D. 儿子想告诉爸爸狗无法理解人类的语言。
data.STORY: Once, Cheng Wei takes his son to the mall and accompanies him to the children's playground. Suddenly, he sees a person leading a dog in. Cheng Wei asks this person, "Don't you see the sign that says no pets are allowed?" The other party appears very disdainful and has no intention of paying attention to Cheng Wei. At this moment, his son laughs and says to Cheng Wei, "Dad, you are so silly, dogs don't know how to read."
data.QUESTION: What does the son really mean when he says this?
data.OPTION-A: The son is mocking this person for lacking social morality.
data.OPTION-B: The son is joking with his father, trying to lighten the mood.
data.OPTION-C: The son likes dogs and hopes to have one.
data.OPTION-D: The son wants to tell his father that dogs can't understand human language.

data.STORY: In the 19th century, in Vienna, Austria, women like to wear a kind of towering hat. data.故事: 刚入职的小李工作态度较为散漫，经常不在公司。一天，他的上司老王叫来小李，说：“我们公司的打卡机好像坏了，看不到你的打卡记录。”

data.OPTION-D: Lao Wang worries that the problem with the time clock affects work, and thinks it needs to be solved promptly.

data.QUESTION: What does Xiao Hua really want to say when he says this?
data.OPTION-A: Xiao Hua is asking about his current location
data.OPTION-B: Xiao Hua wants the girl to read books with him.
data.OPTION-C: Xiao Hua is interested in the music on the girl's phone.
data.OPTION-D: Xiao Hua hints the girl to turn off the music on her phone.

data.故事: 妈妈做完晚餐，来到餐厅和爸爸儿子一起吃饭，看到桌上摆放着两双筷子，说到：“奇怪，今天我们是几个人一起吃饭呀？”
data.问题: 当妈妈说这句话的时候，她真正想说的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 妈妈在询问一起吃饭的人数。
data.选项B: B. 妈妈暗示家里应该有更多的人来。
data.选项C: C. 妈妈暗示应该给她再拿一双筷子。
data.选项D: D. 妈妈暗示她不太饿，可能不会吃太多的食物。
data.STORY: Mom finishes making dinner, comes to the dining room to eat with dad and son, sees two pairs of chopsticks on the table, and says, "Strange, how many of us eat together today?"
data.QUESTION: What does mom really mean when she says this?
data.OPTION-A: Mom is asking about the number of people eating together.
data.OPTION-B: Mom hints that there should be more people coming home.
data.OPTION-C: Mom hints that she should get another pair of chopsticks.
data.OPTION-D: Mom hints that she is not very hungry and may not eat much food.

data.故事: 在公司的一个会议中，经理正在讨论即将到来的产品发布。一名新员工持续地提问，打断了经理的发言。经理看了他一眼，说：“你的热情真是让人佩服。”
data.问题: 当经理说这句话时，他真正想说的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 经理认为这位员工非常热爱工作，对此表示赞赏。
data.选项B: B. 经理暗示这名员工应当在合适的时候提问。
data.选项C: C. 经理期待所有员工都能表现出如此的热情。
data.选项D: D. 经理鼓励新员工继续提问。
data.STORY: In a company meeting, the manager is discussing the upcoming product launch. A new employee keeps asking questions, interrupting the manager's speech. The manager looks at him and says, "Your enthusiasm really impresses people."
data.QUESTION: What does the manager really mean when he says this?
data.OPTION-A: The manager thinks this employee loves his job very much and appreciates it.
data.OPTION-B: The manager implies that this employee should ask questions at the right time.
data.OPTION-C: The manager expects all employees to show such enthusiasm.
data.OPTION-D: The manager encourages the new employee to continue asking questions.

data.故事: 在自习课上上，明明忽然发出了爽朗的笑声。同坐一桌的淑华看过去，笑着对他说：“明明，你的笑声真有特色。”
data.问题: 当淑华说这句话时，她真正想说的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 淑华非常喜欢明明的笑声，并认为它很特别。
data.选项B: B. 淑华暗示明明他的笑声太大了，应该小声一些。
data.选项C: C. 淑华在赞美明明，认为他的笑声有独特的吸引力。
data.选项D: D. 淑华觉得明明的笑声很有趣，让她感到快乐。
data.STORY: In the self-study class, Mingming suddenly gives a hearty laugh. Shuhua, who sits at the same table, looks over and smiles at him, saying, "Mingming, your laughter really has a unique character."
data.QUESTION: What does Shuhua really want to say when she says this?
data.OPTION-A: Shuhua really likes Mingming's laughter and thinks it is very special.
data.OPTION-B: Shuhua hints that Mingming's laughter is too loud and he should be quieter.
data.OPTION-C: Shuhua praises Mingming, thinking his laughter has a unique attraction.
data.OPTION-D: Shuhua finds Mingming's laughter interesting, it makes her happy.

data.故事: 小周和张姐是多年的老朋友，小周是一名医生，在平时在河南一家医院工作，张姐则生活在厦门。国庆假期，小周来到厦门旅游，一天早上，张姐微信问小周：“周医生今天有号不？坐诊不？”
data.问题: 当张姐说这句话的时候，她真正想说的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 张姐想问小周今天能否有空见个面
data.选项B: B. 张姐想问小周是否在他的医院里为病人看病
data.选项C: C. 张姐感到身体不适，需要小周给她看病
data.选项D: D. 张姐想询问小周的医生职业生涯是否顺利
data.STORY: Xiao Zhou and Sister Zhang are old friends for many years. Xiao Zhou is a doctor, he works in a hospital in Henan usually, while Sister Zhang lives in Xiamen. During the National Day holiday, Xiao Zhou comes to Xiamen for a tour. One morning, Sister Zhang asks Xiao Zhou on WeChat: "Doctor Zhou, do you have a number today? Do you see patients?"
data.QUESTION: What does Sister Zhang really mean when she says this?
data.OPTION-A: Sister Zhang wants to ask Xiao Zhou if he can meet today
data.OPTION-B: Sister Zhang wants to ask Xiao Zhou if he is treating patients in his hospital
data.OPTION-C: Sister Zhang feels unwell and needs Xiao Zhou to treat her
data.OPTION-D: Sister Zhang wants to ask about the smoothness of Xiao Zhou's medical career

data.故事: 安娜正在准备开车去家附近的超市购物。她的丈夫汤姆从房间走出来，看了看客厅烧着的炉火说，"看这炉火烧得真旺啊。"
data.问题: 当汤姆说这句话的时候，他真正想说的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 汤姆暗示安娜在出发前应当熄灭客厅的炉火。
data.选项B: B. 汤姆想表达他喜欢看熊熊燃烧的火焰。
data.选项C: C. 汤姆暗示安娜去超市购买一些炉子的燃料。
data.选项D: D. 汤姆希望安娜把炉火烧得更旺一些。
data.STORY: Anna is preparing to drive to the supermarket near her home. Her husband Tom comes out of the room, looks at the burning fire in the living room and says, "Look, this fire is really blazing."
data.QUESTION: What does Tom really want to say when he says this?
data.OPTION-A: Tom implies that Anna should extinguish the fire in the living room before leaving.
data.OPTION-B: Tom wants to express that he likes to watch the blazing flames.
data.OPTION-C: Tom implies that Anna goes to the supermarket to buy some fuel for the stove.
data.OPTION-D: Tom hopes that Anna makes the fire burn more vigorously.

鸿杰去银行帮朋友办事，朋友在外地，他找到工作人员要来了办事需要填写的表单，看到了签名那栏，愣住了，因为显示要本人签字。

data.STORY:
Hongjie goes to the bank to help a friend with some business. His friend is out of town. He gets the form that needs to be filled out from the staff and stops when he sees the signature column because it requires the person's own signature.
He asks the staff very straightforwardly: "My friend is out of town, can I sign for him?"
The staff says: "There is surveillance here, it is impossible for others to sign on behalf, go find the person to sign."
He says anxiously: "My friend really can't come back, please make it convenient."
The staff still says: "There is surveillance here, others can't sign on behalf, go find the person to sign."
data.QUESTION: What does the staff really mean when he says this?
data.OPTION-A: The staff is insisting that Hongjie must find his friend to come to the bank to sign.
data.OPTION-B: The staff is hinting that Hongjie can sign for his friend after leaving the bank.
data.OPTION-C: The staff is reconfirming the rule that the bank does not allow others to sign on behalf.
data.OPTION-D: The staff is suggesting that Hongjie find a suitable signing tool.

data.故事: 小杨所在的公司周三有周例会。某周一，领导带着小王去会见客户张局，两人一直相谈甚欢，但谈的都是一些无关痛痒的话题，因为正事存在观点分歧。眼看着将近饭点，出现了下面几句对话： 领导：“张局，快到饭点了，看您有时间吗？想约您吃个饭？” 然后领导转过身，边眨眼睛，边对小杨说：“小杨，咱们晚上单位还有会议吗？”
data.问题: 当领导问小杨这个问题的时候，他的目的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 领导想向小杨询问会议时间，以安排和客户的饭局。
data.选项B: B. 领导希望小杨回答今晚有会议，以此借口结束会面。
data.选项C: C.领导想了解小杨对周例会的准备情况。
data.选项D: D. 领导希望询问小杨愿不愿不参加会议，而陪他们吃饭。
data.STORY: Xiao Yang's company holds a weekly meeting every Wednesday. On a certain Monday, the leader takes Xiao Wang to meet with client Director Zhang. The two of them chat happily, but they only talk about some irrelevant topics because there are disagreements on the main issues. As it approaches mealtime, the following conversation occurs: Leader: "Director Zhang, it is almost mealtime, do you have time? I want to invite you to have a meal." Then the leader turns around, winks, and says to Xiao Yang: "Xiao Yang, do we have a meeting at the unit tonight?"
data.QUESTION: What is the leader's purpose when he asks Xiao Yang this question?
data.OPTION-A: The leader wants to ask Xiao Yang about the meeting time to arrange a meal with the client.
data.OPTION-B: The leader hopes Xiao Yang answers that there is a meeting tonight, so he can use this as an excuse to end the meeting.
data.OPTION-C: The leader wants to understand Xiao Yang's preparation for the weekly meeting.
data.OPTION-D: The leader wants to ask if Xiao Yang is willing to skip the meeting and join them for dinner.

data.故事: 小汪和网络上认识的女生小兰的见面约在了酒店。在前台，小兰不愿意出示身份证登记。 前台工作人员问：“您是一位还是两位？两位的话需要出示双方身份证的先生。” 小汪回头看着小兰，她慢慢走到沙发边上坐下仍然没有出示身份证的意思。于是小汪转过头问：“两位，那怎么办？” 此时前台工作人员又问：“您是一位入住还是两位呢？”
data.问题: 当工作人员提出这个问题的时候，他的目的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 他没有听清楚小汪之前的回答，要再进行确认。
data.选项B: B. 他正在重新核实小汪的住宿需求。
data.选项C: C. 他暗示小汪可回答一位入住，这样只需要用一个人的身份证。
data.选项D: D. 他暗示不出示两人身份证就不可以一起住宿。
data.STORY: Xiao Wang and the girl he meets online, Xiao Lan, arrange to meet at a hotel. At the front desk, Xiao Lan does not want to show her ID for registration. The front desk staff asks, "Are you one or two? If two, the gentleman needs to show both IDs." Xiao Wang turns his head and looks at Xiao Lan, she slowly walks to the edge of the sofa and sits down, still showing no intention of showing her ID. So Xiao Wang turns his head and asks, "Two, what to do?" At this time, the front desk staff asks again, "Are you checking in for one or two?"
data.QUESTION: What is his purpose when the staff asks this question?
data.OPTION-A: He does not hear Xiao Wang's previous answer clearly and needs to confirm again.
data.OPTION-B: He is re-verifying Xiao Wang's accommodation needs.
data.OPTION-C: He hints that Xiao Wang can answer one person checks in, so only one person's ID is needed.
data.OPTION-D: He hints that if they do not show both IDs, they cannot stay together.

data.STORY: Fitness coach Zhang Jiali drives without a seatbelt one time and a traffic cop catches her. The traffic cop comes over and asks Zhang Jiali, "Why don't you wear a seatbelt? Are you pregnant?"

data.STORY: One day, Xiao Ming passes by a small alley, there is a small stall at the entrance of the alley that sells fried goods. Xiao Ming feels a bit strange, but doesn't think much about it, takes the money and is about to walk away, Zhang San, who is passing by, says to himself, "Your melon seeds, they don't look like the real thing." data.故事: 在一次与朋友的社交活动中，Sophie试图维持团体的欢乐氛围，但是她的朋友Tom开始分享了一些陈年旧事，使大家感觉很不舒服。Sophie拿起一根玉米棒吃了起来，看着Tom说：“Tom，玉米棒真是太好吃了，你也来试试吧！”
data.问题: 当Sophie说这句话的时候，他真正想说的是什么？

data.OPTION-B: Sophie thinks Tom should pay attention to his diet.
data.OPTION-C: Sophie hopes Tom stops sharing things that make everyone feel uncomfortable.
data.OPTION-D: Sophie wants to invite Tom to enjoy a pleasant meal time together.

data.故事: 小红大概晚上9点到达火车站候车厅，进入后，她询问乘务员“这里可以待多久？”。乘务员回答：“最多三个小时，也就是到12点，你要不要现在就进去？”小红说：“可以的，我是凌晨3点的火车，我想着在这里休息到12点，出去再呆2个多小时。”此时，然后乘务员突然提醒说：“注意听广播提醒你上列车，不要误车。”
data.问题: 乘务员说这句话的时候，真正的意思是什么？
data.选项A: A. 乘务员在暗示小红可以在候车厅一直休息，直到上车。
data.选项B: B. 乘务员在告诫小红，夜晚出行安全问题需要提高警惕。
data.选项C: C. 乘务员在告诉小红，她必须在12点之前离开候车厅。
data.选项D: D. 乘务员在提醒小红要关注列车时刻表，以防错过火车。
data.STORY: Xiao Hong probably arrives at the train station waiting room at about 9 pm. After entering, she asks the conductor, "How long can I stay here?". The conductor replies, "Up to three hours, which is until 12 o'clock, do you want to go in now?" Xiao Hong says, "Yes, I am on the 3 am train, I think about resting here until 12 o'clock, then go out and stay for more than 2 hours." At this time, the conductor suddenly reminds, "Pay attention to the broadcast to remind you to get on the train, do not miss the train."
data.QUESTION: What is the real meaning when the conductor says this?
data.OPTION-A: The conductor implies that Xiao Hong can rest in the waiting room until she boards the train.
data.OPTION-B: The conductor warns Xiao Hong that she needs to be vigilant about safety issues when traveling at night.
data.OPTION-C: The conductor tells Xiao Hong that she must leave the waiting room before 12 o'clock.
data.OPTION-D: The conductor reminds Xiao Hong to pay attention to the train schedule to prevent missing the train.

data.故事: 小李在参加驾驶员路考时较为紧张，一进入车内就想要启动发动机。考官在旁边询问，“你准备好了吗！” 小李说：“准备好了！” 考官把自己的安全带拆开又系上，又问了小李一次“你准备好了吗？”
data.问题: 考官说这句话的时候，真正的意思是什么？
data.选项A: A. 考官在询问小李是否有考试压力。
data.选项B: B. 考官正在确认小李是否真的准备好开始测试。
data.选项C: C. 考官在提醒小李系好安全带后再启动发动机。
data.选项D: D. 考官在测试小李对重复问题的耐心。
data.STORY: Xiao Li is quite nervous when participating in the driver's road test, and wants to start the engine as soon as he gets in the car. The examiner asks next to him, "Are you ready!" Xiao Li says, "I am ready!" The examiner unbuckles his seat belt and buckles it again, and asks Xiao Li again, "Are you ready?"
data.QUESTION: What is the real meaning when the examiner says this?
data.OPTION-A: The examiner is asking if Xiao Li is under exam pressure.
data.OPTION-B: The examiner is confirming whether Xiao Li is really ready to start the test.
data.OPTION-C: The examiner is reminding Xiao Li to buckle up the seat belt before starting the engine.
data.OPTION-D: The examiner is testing Xiao Li's patience with repeated questions.

data.故事: 刚刚入职的小王和老科长一起在疫情管控点站岗，站岗任务不繁重，但老科长站半天感觉很累。不巧的是管控点设备简陋，只有一个凳子。老科长对小王说“小王同志，你也站半天了，就一个凳子，你坐一会儿吧”
data.问题: 老科长说这句话时，他真正的意图是什么？
data.选项A: A. 老科长希望小王将凳子让给他坐。
data.选项B: B. 老科长是在关心小王的健康，希望小王坐下休息。
data.选项C: C. 老科长想要把坐着的时间让给小王，自己选择站着。
data.选项D: D. 老科长希望引发关于工作设备状况的对话。
data.STORY: Newly joined Xiao Wang and the old section chief stand guard together at the epidemic control point. The guard duty is not heavy, but the old section chief feels very tired after standing for half a day. Unfortunately, the equipment at the control point is simple, there is only one stool. The old section chief says to Xiao Wang, "Comrade Xiao Wang, you also stand for half a day, there is only one stool, you sit for a while."
data.QUESTION: What is the real intention of the old section chief when he says this?
data.OPTION-A: The old section chief hopes Xiao Wang gives him the stool to sit.
data.OPTION-B: The old section chief cares about Xiao Wang's health and hopes Xiao Wang sits down to rest.
data.OPTION-C: The old section chief wants to give the sitting time to Xiao Wang and chooses to stand himself.
data.OPTION-D: The old section chief hopes to initiate a conversation about the condition of the work equipment.

data.故事: 小月热爱阅读，但家里的书架空间已经不够她的新书了。她对她的爸爸说：“爸爸，你看书架上的书快要堆到天花板上去了。”
data.问题: 当小月说这句话时，她真正想说的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 小月想要爸爸把部分书捐出去。
data.选项B: B. 小月希望爸爸能够帮她卖掉一些旧书。
data.选项C: C. 小月希望爸爸给她买一个更大的书架。
data.选项D: D. 小月希望爸爸赶快卖掉家里的其他不必要的物体以为新书腾出空间。
data.STORY: Xiaoyue loves reading, but the space on the bookshelf at home is not enough for her new books. She says to her father, "Dad, you see the books on the shelf are about to pile up to the ceiling."
data.QUESTION: What does Xiaoyue really want to say when she says this?
data.OPTION-A: Xiaoyue wants her father to donate some of the books.
data.OPTION-B: Xiaoyue hopes her father can help her sell some old books.
data.OPTION-C: Xiaoyue hopes her father buys her a bigger bookshelf.
data.OPTION-D: Xiaoyue hopes her father quickly sells other unnecessary items at home to make room for new books.

data.故事: 最近小华从外国回来参加了一场宴会，在餐桌上，主办方自带了许多茅台酒。开场后不久，小华的朋友，品酒经验丰富的小张喝了一口桌上的茅台酒，说了一句：“茅台就是不一样啊，味道好。”，随后找了个借口换喝了红酒。
data.问题: 小张说这句话时，他真正想说的意思是什么？
data.选项A: A. 小张喜欢喝红酒，不喜欢茅台酒
data.选项B: B. 小张认为茅台酒的品质优于红酒
data.选项C: C. 小张暗示主办方的茅台酒可能不是真的
data.选项D: D. 小张认为这个宴会的酒品种应该更多样
data.STORY: Recently, Xiaohua comes back from abroad and attends a banquet. At the table, the host brings a lot of Maotai liquor. Not long after the start, Xiaohua's friend, the experienced wine taster Xiaozhang, takes a sip of the Maotai on the table and says, "Maotai is different, it tastes good.", then finds an excuse to switch to red wine.
data.QUESTION: What does Xiaozhang really mean when he says this?
data.OPTION-A: Xiaozhang likes to drink red wine, not Maotai
data.OPTION-B: Xiaozhang thinks the quality of Maotai is better than red wine
data.OPTION-C: Xiaozhang hints that the host's Maotai may not be real

data.故事: 刘伟是一个身材魁梧的肌肉男，某天他第一次去岳父家，吃完了一碗米饭后，给大家讲了个故事：“前几天我到山里去，见到一只大老虎，那虎爪啊……”将空碗往桌上一倒扣，“有这么大！” 岳父立即想到是刘伟还没吃饱，就默默转身进厨房准备给他添饭。结果到了厨房一看，已经没有饭了。岳父略一思索就抱着锅出来，把空锅往桌上一倒扣：“那老虎头是不是有这么大？”
data.问题: 岳父说这句话时，真正想说的意思是什么？
data.选项A: A. 岳父暗示他曾经亲见过一只大老虎
data.选项B: B. 岳父想提醒刘伟不要吹嘘自己的勇气
data.选项C: C. 岳父暗示锅中已经没有饭了
data.选项D: D. 岳父在揶揄刘伟的吃相
data.STORY: Liu Wei is a muscular man with a robust figure. One day, he goes to his father-in-law's house for the first time. After finishing a bowl of rice, he tells everyone a story: "A few days ago, I go to the mountain and see a big tiger, its claws..." He turns the empty bowl upside down on the table, "are this big!" The father-in-law immediately thinks that Liu Wei is still hungry, so he silently turns around and goes into the kitchen to get him more rice. But when he gets to the kitchen, there is no rice left. After a brief thought, the father-in-law comes out with the pot, turns the empty pot upside down on the table: "Is the tiger's head this big?"
data.QUESTION: What does the father-in-law really mean when he says this?
data.OPTION-A: The father-in-law hints that he once sees a big tiger
data.OPTION-B: The father-in-law wants to remind Liu Wei not to boast about his courage
data.OPTION-C: The father-in-law hints that there is no rice left in the pot
data.OPTION-D: The father-in-law is teasing Liu Wei's eating manners

data.故事: 李明是一个小学五年级的学生，最近喜欢上了一个流行的电子游戏。由于游戏太过迷人，他每天花费很多时间在这款游戏上。一天，妈妈对正在玩游戏的李明说：“你的游戏水平最近突飞猛进嘛。”

data.选项D: D. 妈妈暗示李明最近花费太多时间在游戏上了。
data.STORY: Li Ming is a fifth-grade elementary school student who recently falls in love with a popular electronic game. data.QUESTION: What does she really mean when she says these words?

data.OPTION-D: Mother hints that Li Ming spends too much time on the game recently.

data.选项D: D. 赵老师希望同学们能够理解教师上课的辛劳。

data.QUESTION: What does Teacher Zhao really want to say when she says this?
data.OPTION-A: Teacher Zhao thinks her class is boring, this is her way of apologizing to the students.
data.OPTION-B: Teacher Zhao wants the students to give her suggestions on how to make the class more interesting.
data.OPTION-C: Teacher Zhao implies that all students should focus their attention on the class.
data.OPTION-D: Teacher Zhao hopes that the students can understand the hard work of teaching.

data.故事: 在自习课上上，明明忽然发出了爽朗的笑声。同坐一桌的淑华看过去，笑着对他说：“明明，你的笑声真有特色。”
data.问题: 当淑华说这句话时，她真正想说的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 淑华非常喜欢明明的笑声，并认为它很特别。
data.选项B: B. 淑华暗示明明他的笑声太大了，应该小声一些。
data.选项C: C. 淑华在赞美明明，认为他的笑声有独特的吸引力。
data.选项D: D. 淑华觉得明明的笑声很有趣，让她感到快乐。
data.STORY: In the self-study class, Mingming suddenly gives a hearty laugh. Shuhua, who sits at the same table, looks over and smiles at him, saying, "Mingming, your laughter really has a unique character."
data.QUESTION: What does Shuhua really want to say when she says this?
data.OPTION-A: Shuhua really likes Mingming's laughter and thinks it is very special.
data.OPTION-B: Shuhua hints that Mingming's laughter is too loud and he should be quieter.
data.OPTION-C: Shuhua praises Mingming, thinking his laughter has a unique attraction.
data.OPTION-D: Shuhua finds Mingming's laughter interesting, it makes her happy.

output:
[[D]]最有可能。根据情景分析，如果在晚课自习还笑得那么开怀，这不是让老师或其他同学感到宽慰的，虽然重点并不是明明的坏事，若他这样朝着完全没人اه谝的时候....

话说回来他有作为整个课时的整体氛围，并把淑华的话说明明笑出了她的芳心，而且无疑的环境氛围并不是全然的好，也很可能会通过淑华的话来说服小明在课间停止非说往更办法吧。其实这句话更爵是什么意思。

data.OPTION-A: The boss hopes that Chen Wei gets off the car safely to avoid falling.
data.OPTION-B: The boss hopes that Chen Wei checks the current market price of oranges with his phone.

data.OPTION-D: The boss suggests that Chen Wei personally selects and checks the quality of the oranges.

data.故事: 张霞是装修公司的员工，有个同学是开养生馆的，经常在朋友圈讲吃素的好处。一次张霞请他吃饭，专门给他点了全素宴。他问张霞：“你们搞装修的，下班回家会不会经常装装这里，修修那里？”
data.问题: 当张霞的同学说这句话时，他真正想说的是什么？

data.选项D: D. 他想要张霞帮助他装修养生馆。
data.STORY: Zhang Xia is an employee of a decoration company, and a classmate runs a health spa and often talks about the benefits of vegetarianism in his circle of friends. Once Zhang Xia invites him to dinner and specifically orders a full vegetarian feast for him. He asks Zhang Xia, "Do you guys who do decoration, when you get off work and go home, do you often decorate here and fix there?"
data.QUESTION: What does he really mean when Zhang Xia's classmate says this?
data.OPTION-A: He is interested in decoration and wants to know more about this industry.
data.OPTION-B: He implies that he does not eat vegetarian every day and suggests Zhang Xia to order some meat dishes.
data.OPTION-C: He thinks Zhang Xia works too hard and should change a job.
data.OPTION-D: He wants Zhang Xia to help him decorate the health spa.

data.故事:
一个理科男生每晚都去一个教室自习，每次都坐在一个不认识的女生后面。渐渐地，男生喜欢上了女生，但一直没有勇气表白。舍友们知道后，全都鼓励他。一天晚上，男生终于鼓足了勇气，写了一封表白信，递到女生的手里。

data.选项C: C. 她不想和男生在一起。
data.选项D: D. 她暗示自己同意了男生的表白。
data.STORY: A science male student goes to a classroom to study every night, always sitting behind a girl he does not know. data.OPTION-A: She indicates that she wants to go home and asks if the boy also wants to go home.
data.OPTION-B: She hopes the boy understands that she needs to be alone.
data.OPTION-C: She does not want to be with the boy.
data.OPTION-D: She implies that she agrees with the boy's confession.

data.故事: 某天小明路过一条小巷，巷口有家小摊在卖炒货。因为小明很喜欢吃瓜子，就上前购买了两斤，在购买时小明递给老板一张百元大钞，老板接过钱，低头和老板娘嘀咕几句，又把前一张钞票递了出来，说：“找不开，没零钱。”小明感到有些奇怪，但也没多想，接过钱正想走开，旁边路过的张三自言自语般地说了一句“你这瓜子，不像真货啊。” 说完张三就走了，老板只勾着头不吭声。
data.问题: 当张三说这句话的时候，他真正想说的是什么？
data.选项A: A.张三在暗示老板把小明的真钞换成了假钞。
data.选项B: B.张三在提醒小明这家小摊可能在售卖假瓜子。
data.选项C: C.张三在讽刺小明喜欢吃的瓜子品种质量较差。
data.选项D: D.张三在表示看不起小明购买瓜子这种行为。
data.STORY: One day, Xiao Ming passes by a small alley, there is a small stall at the entrance of the alley that sells fried goods. Because Xiao Ming likes to eat melon seeds very much, he steps forward to buy two pounds. When buying, Xiao Ming gives the boss a hundred yuan bill, the boss takes the money, lowers his head and mutters a few words with the boss lady, and then hands out the previous bill, saying, "I can't make change, no small change." Xiao Ming feels a bit strange, but doesn't think much about it, takes the money and is about to walk away, Zhang San, who is passing by, says to himself, "Your melon seeds, they don't look like the real thing." After saying this, Zhang San walks away, and the boss just lowers his head and says nothing.
data.QUESTION: What does Zhang San really want to say when he says this?
data.OPTION-A: Zhang San is hinting that the boss changes Xiao Ming's real money into counterfeit money.
data.OPTION-B: Zhang San is reminding Xiao Ming that this small stall may be selling fake melon seeds.
data.OPTION-C: Zhang San is mocking that the quality of the melon seeds Xiao Ming likes to eat is poor.
data.OPTION-D: Zhang San is expressing his disdain for Xiao Ming's behavior of buying melon seeds.

data.问题: 领导说这句话的时候，真正的意图是什么？

data.故事: 小红大概晚上9点到达火车站候车厅，进入后，她询问乘务员“这里可以待多久？”。乘务员回答：“最多三个小时，也就是到12点，你要不要现在就进去？”小红说：“可以的，我是凌晨3点的火车，我想着在这里休息到12点，出去再呆2个多小时。”此时，然后乘务员突然提醒说：“注意听广播提醒你上列车，不要误车。”
data.问题: 乘务员说这句话的时候，真正的意思是什么？
data.选项A: A. 乘务员在暗示小红可以在候车厅一直休息，直到上车。
data.选项B: B. 乘务员在告诫小红，夜晚出行安全问题需要提高警惕。
data.选项C: C. 乘务员在告诉小红，她必须在12点之前离开候车厅。
data.选项D: D. 乘务员在提醒小红要关注列车时刻表，以防错过火车。
data.STORY: Xiao Hong probably arrives at the train station waiting room at about 9 pm. After entering, she asks the conductor, "How long can I stay here?". The conductor replies, "Up to three hours, which is until 12 o'clock, do you want to go in now?" Xiao Hong says, "Yes, I am on the 3 am train, I think about resting here until 12 o'clock, then go out and stay for more than 2 hours." At this time, the conductor suddenly reminds, "Pay attention to the broadcast to remind you to get on the train, do not miss the train."
data.QUESTION: What is the real meaning when the conductor says this?
data.OPTION-A: The conductor implies that Xiao Hong can rest in the waiting room until she boards the train.
data.OPTION-B: The conductor warns Xiao Hong that she needs to be vigilant about safety issues when traveling at night.
data.OPTION-C: The conductor tells Xiao Hong that she must leave the waiting room before 12 o'clock.
data.OPTION-D: The conductor reminds Xiao Hong to pay attention to the train schedule to prevent missing the train.

data.故事: 小李在参加驾驶员路考时较为紧张，一进入车内就想要启动发动机。考官在旁边询问，“你准备好了吗！” 小李说：“准备好了！” 考官把自己的安全带拆开又系上，又问了小李一次“你准备好了吗？”
data.问题: 考官说这句话的时候，真正的意思是什么？
data.选项A: A. 考官在询问小李是否有考试压力。
data.选项B: B. 考官正在确认小李是否真的准备好开始测试。
data.选项C: C. 考官在提醒小李系好安全带后再启动发动机。
data.选项D: D. 考官在测试小李对重复问题的耐心。
data.STORY: Xiao Li is quite nervous when participating in the driver's road test, and wants to start the engine as soon as he gets in the car. The examiner asks next to him, "Are you ready!" Xiao Li says, "I am ready!" The examiner unbuckles his seat belt and buckles it again, and asks Xiao Li again, "Are you ready?"
data.QUESTION: What is the real meaning when the examiner says this?
data.OPTION-A: The examiner is asking if Xiao Li is under exam pressure.
data.OPTION-B: The examiner is confirming whether Xiao Li is really ready to start the test.
data.OPTION-C: The examiner is reminding Xiao Li to buckle up the seat belt before starting the engine.
data.OPTION-D: The examiner is testing Xiao Li's patience with repeated questions.

data.问题: 当儿子说这句话时，他真正想说的意思是什么？
data.选项A: A. 儿子在讽刺这个人没有社会公德。

data.STORY: Once, Cheng Wei takes his son to the mall and accompanies him to the children's playground. Suddenly, he sees a person leading a dog in. At this moment, his son laughs and says to Cheng Wei, "Dad, you are so silly, dogs don't know how to read."
data.QUESTION: What does the son really mean when he says this?
data.OPTION-A: The son is mocking this person for lacking social morality.
data.OPTION-B: The son is joking with his father, trying to lighten the mood.
data.OPTION-C: The son likes dogs and hopes to have one.
data.OPTION-D: The son wants to tell his father that dogs can't understand human language.

data.故事: 19世纪，在奥地利的维也纳，妇女们喜欢戴一种高高耸起的帽子。她们进剧场看戏也不愿将帽子摘下，以致后排的观众被挡住了视线。经理上台请在座的女观众将帽子摘下来，然而说了半天妇女们也不予以理睬。最后经理又补充了一句：“那么，这样吧，年纪大一点的女士可以照顾，不必脱帽。”
data.问题: 剧场经理说这些话时，他真正想说的意思是什么？
data.选项A: A. 他希望所有的女士都将帽子摘下来。
data.选项B: B. 他只希望年纪轻的女士将帽子摘下来。
data.选项C: C. 他对戴帽子的女士感到恼火。
data.选项D: D. 他在夸赞年纪大的女士的优雅。
data.STORY: In the 19th century, in Vienna, Austria, women like to wear a kind of towering hat. They go to the theater to watch plays and do not want to take off their hats, so the audience in the back row is blocked. The manager goes on stage to ask the female audience to take off their hats, but the women ignore him after a long talk. Finally, the manager adds one more sentence: "So, like this, older ladies can take care, no need to take off the hat."
data.QUESTION: When the theater manager says these words, what does he really want to say?
data.OPTION-A: He hopes all ladies take off their hats.
data.OPTION-B: He only hopes young ladies take off their hats.
data.OPTION-C: He is annoyed with the ladies wearing hats.
data.OPTION-D: He is praising the elegance of older ladies.

data.故事: 老王在公司最牛的团队中工作，团队中每个人都有很强的工作能力。他是一个完美主义者，不能忍受工作中的任何一点瑕疵。一次工作会议中，老王总结了当前工作中存在的诸多细节问题。下属小张突然问老王：“老王，你喜欢吃鱼吗？”

data.STORY: Lao Wang works in the most powerful team in the company, and everyone in the team has strong work ability. He is a perfectionist and cannot tolerate any flaws in his work. In a work meeting, Lao Wang summarizes many detail problems that exist in the current work. Subordinate Xiao Zhang suddenly asks Lao Wang, "Lao Wang, do you like to eat fish?"
data.QUESTION: What does Xiao Zhang really mean when he says these words?
data.OPTION-A: Xiao Zhang is asking about Lao Wang's eating habits in order to invite Old Wang to eat in the future.
data.OPTION-B: Xiao Zhang wants to invite Lao Wang to eat fish to promote their relationship.
data.OPTION-C: Xiao Zhang is mocking Lao Wang for being picky.
data.OPTION-D: Xiao Zhang wants to change the topic to ease the tension of the work meeting.

data.选项D: D. 班主任想让小简早点休息以保持健康。

data.故事: 小雨和小华是一对恋人。一天，小雨将两人身份证放一起，说是比谁更好看，小华说：“比对不是得同样的灯光，同样的摄影师，同等条件下才能得出正确的结论吗？改天我们一起去拍证件照？”
data.问题: 当小华说这句话的时候，他真正想说的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 小华希望换一个摄影师重新拍摄他和小雨的证件照。
data.选项B: B. 小华觉得自己的证件照拍摄的不满意，希望重新拍摄。
data.选项C: C. 小华建议两人去办理结婚登记。
data.选项D: D. 小华希望他和小雨购买一套专业的摄影设备。
data.STORY: Xiaoyu and Xiaohua are a couple. One day, Xiaoyu puts their IDs together, saying it is to see who looks better, Xiaohua says, "Doesn't the comparison require the same lighting, the same photographer, and the same conditions to reach a correct conclusion? Shall we go take ID photos together another day?"
data.QUESTION: What does Xiaohua really want to say when he says this?
data.OPTION-A: Xiaohua hopes to hire a new photographer to retake his and Xiaoyu's ID photos.
data.OPTION-B: Xiaohua is not satisfied with his ID photo and hopes to retake it.
data.OPTION-C: Xiaohua suggests that they go to register for marriage.
data.OPTION-D: Xiaohua hopes that he and Xiaoyu buy a set of professional photography equipment.

data.故事: 公司会议室里开会，员工小李正打瞌睡，经理对他说：“小李，昨天工作到很晚吧，要注意休息。”
data.问题: 当经理说这句话的时候，他真正想说的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 经理在提醒小李，他应该充分休息，以免因缺乏瞌睡而影响工作效能。
data.选项B: B. 经理在赞扬小李，他工作异常努力，即使在夜晚也在工作。
data.选项C: C. 经理在询问小李，他昨晚是不是熬夜工作，所以今天无法专心。
data.选项D: D. 经理在提醒小李，他在开会的时候应该保持精神。
data.STORY: A meeting is happening in the company conference room, employee Xiao Li is dozing off, the manager says to him: "Xiao Li, you work until very late yesterday, you need to pay attention to rest."
data.QUESTION: What does the manager really mean when he says this?
data.OPTION-A: The manager is reminding Xiao Li that he should rest fully to avoid affecting work efficiency due to lack of sleep.
data.OPTION-B: The manager is praising Xiao Li, he works extremely hard, even at night.
data.OPTION-C: The manager is asking Xiao Li if he stays up late to work last night, so he can't concentrate today.
data.OPTION-D: The manager is reminding Xiao Li that he should stay alert during the meeting.

data.故事:
鸿杰去银行帮朋友办事，朋友在外地，他找到工作人员要来了办事需要填写的表单，看到了签名那栏，愣住了，因为显示要本人签字。
他很耿直的问工作人员：“我朋友在外地，我可以代签吗？”
工作人员说：“这里有监控，是没法别人代签的，出去找本人签。”
他很着急的说：“我朋友真的回不来，行个方便吧。”
工作人员还是那句话：“这里有监控，别人没法代签，出去找本人签。”
data.问题: 当工作人员说这句话时，他真正想说的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 工作人员是在硬性要求鸿杰必须找他的朋友来银行签字。
data.选项B: B. 工作人员在暗示鸿杰可以走出银行后帮朋友代签。
data.选项C: C. 工作人员是再次确认了规定，即银行内不允许他人代签。
data.选项D: D. 工作人员是在建议鸿杰去找合适的签字工具。
data.STORY:
Hongjie goes to the bank to help a friend with some business. His friend is out of town. He gets the form that needs to be filled out from the staff and stops when he sees the signature column because it requires the person's own signature.
He asks the staff very straightforwardly: "My friend is out of town, can I sign for him?"
The staff says: "There is surveillance here, it is impossible for others to sign on behalf, go find the person to sign."
He says anxiously: "My friend really can't come back, please make it convenient."
The staff still says: "There is surveillance here, others can't sign on behalf, go find the person to sign."
data.QUESTION: What does the staff really mean when he says this?
data.OPTION-A: The staff is insisting that Hongjie must find his friend to come to the bank to sign.
data.OPTION-B: The staff is hinting that Hongjie can sign for his friend after leaving the bank.
data.OPTION-C: The staff is reconfirming the rule that the bank does not allow others to sign on behalf.
data.OPTION-D: The staff is suggesting that Hongjie find a suitable signing tool.

data.问题: 当邻居的妈妈说这句话时，她真正想说的是什么？

data.STORY: Yue Sheng often goes to a neighbor's house of the same age to play at night when he is a child. One day, he plays until late at night, his mother comes to him before going to bed and says, "Come to play again tomorrow." Yue Sheng feels invited, he doesn't really want to play with him the next day, but in order not to disappoint this kindness, he reluctantly goes to his house to play until midnight. His mother comes to him before going to bed and says, "Come to play again tomorrow."
data.QUESTION: What does the neighbor's mother really mean when she says this?
data.OPTION-A: She really likes Yue Sheng.
data.OPTION-B: She hopes Yue Sheng comes to her house to play every day.
data.OPTION-C: She hints that Yue Sheng should leave.
data.OPTION-D: She thinks Yue Sheng is a friend who brings fun to her son.

data.STORY: Wang Yuan breaks up with his girlfriend for a year already. After that, Wang Yuan experiences changes and faces unemployment, so he starts to install the Didi taxi app to run online car-hailing. One day, he picks up a female passenger, who turns out to be his ex-girlfriend. Along the way, the two are silent, the ex-girlfriend's expression struggles, as if she is making some mental preparation. After arriving at the destination, she quietly asks Wang Yuan: "Can we go back?" Wang Yuan lights a cigarette, struggles for a long time and says: "Go back? Going back costs an extra twenty!"
data.QUESTION: When Wang Yuan says this sentence, what does he really want to say?
data.OPTION-A: He wants to express his willingness to reconcile with his ex-girlfriend, but the premise is to increase the fee.
data.OPTION-B: He expresses his willingness to take his ex-girlfriend back to the place where he picks her up, the premise is to increase the fee
data.OPTION-C: He expresses the hope that his ex-girlfriend understands his current economic difficulties.
data.OPTION-D: He indicates his refusal to the ex-girlfriend's reconciliation request.

data.故事:
一个理科男生每晚都去一个教室自习，每次都坐在一个不认识的女生后面。渐渐地，男生喜欢上了女生，但一直没有勇气表白。舍友们知道后，全都鼓励他。一天晚上，男生终于鼓足了勇气，写了一封表白信，递到女生的手里。
女生看了一会儿之后，收拾学习用具，转身对男生说：我想回去了，你呢？
data.问题: 当女生说出这句话时，她真正想说的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 她表明自己要回家了，询问男生是否也要回家。
data.选项B: B. 她希望男生可以明白她需要独处。
data.选项C: C. 她不想和男生在一起。
data.选项D: D. 她暗示自己同意了男生的表白。
data.STORY: A science male student goes to a classroom to study every night, always sitting behind a girl he does not know. Gradually, the boy falls in love with the girl, but he never has the courage to confess. When his roommates know, they all encourage him. One night, the boy finally gathers the courage, writes a love letter, and gives it to the girl.\nThe girl looks at it for a while, packs up her study tools, turns around and says to the boy: I want to go back, what about you?
data.QUESTION: What does she really want to say when the girl says this sentence?
data.OPTION-A: She indicates that she wants to go home and asks if the boy also wants to go home.
data.OPTION-B: She hopes the boy understands that she needs to be alone.
data.OPTION-C: She does not want to be with the boy.
data.OPTION-D: She implies that she agrees with the boy's confession.

output:
推理分析：
女生收拾学习用具，转身对男生说“我想回去了，你呢？”这句话的语气似乎比较平淡，没有明显的拒绝或接纳的印象。然而，这anceled表达她的感受以及状态。当女生说这句话时，她很可能是想要表达自己的需要时间独处，而不是询问男生是否要回家。

最可能的答案是 C. 她希望男生可以明白她需要独处。 

那么最终的答案是 [[C]]。

data.QUESTION: What is his purpose when the staff asks this question?

data.STORY: One day, Xiao Ming passes by a small alley, there is a small stall at the entrance of the alley that sells fried goods. Because Xiao Ming likes to eat melon seeds very much, he steps forward to buy two pounds. When buying, Xiao Ming gives the boss a hundred yuan bill, the boss takes the money, lowers his head and mutters a few words with the boss lady, and then hands out the previous bill, saying, "I can't make change, no small change." Xiao Ming feels a bit strange, but doesn't think much about it, takes the money and is about to walk away, Zhang San, who is passing by, says to himself, "Your melon seeds, they don't look like the real thing." After saying this, Zhang San walks away, and the boss just lowers his head and says nothing.
data.QUESTION: What does Zhang San really want to say when he says this?

data.OPTION-C: Zhang San is mocking that the quality of the melon seeds Xiao Ming likes to eat is poor.
data.OPTION-D: Zhang San is expressing his disdain for Xiao Ming's behavior of buying melon seeds.

data.故事: 小红大概晚上9点到达火车站候车厅，进入后，她询问乘务员“这里可以待多久？”。乘务员回答：“最多三个小时，也就是到12点，你要不要现在就进去？”小红说：“可以的，我是凌晨3点的火车，我想着在这里休息到12点，出去再呆2个多小时。”此时，然后乘务员突然提醒说：“注意听广播提醒你上列车，不要误车。”
data.问题: 乘务员说这句话的时候，真正的意思是什么？
data.选项A: A. 乘务员在暗示小红可以在候车厅一直休息，直到上车。
data.选项B: B. 乘务员在告诫小红，夜晚出行安全问题需要提高警惕。
data.选项C: C. 乘务员在告诉小红，她必须在12点之前离开候车厅。
data.选项D: D. 乘务员在提醒小红要关注列车时刻表，以防错过火车。
data.STORY: Xiao Hong probably arrives at the train station waiting room at about 9 pm. After entering, she asks the conductor, "How long can I stay here?". The conductor replies, "Up to three hours, which is until 12 o'clock, do you want to go in now?" Xiao Hong says, "Yes, I am on the 3 am train, I think about resting here until 12 o'clock, then go out and stay for more than 2 hours." At this time, the conductor suddenly reminds, "Pay attention to the broadcast to remind you to get on the train, do not miss the train."
data.QUESTION: What is the real meaning when the conductor says this?
data.OPTION-A: The conductor implies that Xiao Hong can rest in the waiting room until she boards the train.
data.OPTION-B: The conductor warns Xiao Hong that she needs to be vigilant about safety issues when traveling at night.
data.OPTION-C: The conductor tells Xiao Hong that she must leave the waiting room before 12 o'clock.
data.OPTION-D: The conductor reminds Xiao Hong to pay attention to the train schedule to prevent missing the train.

data.故事: 小李在参加驾驶员路考时较为紧张，一进入车内就想要启动发动机。考官在旁边询问，“你准备好了吗！” 小李说：“准备好了！” 考官把自己的安全带拆开又系上，又问了小李一次“你准备好了吗？”
data.问题: 考官说这句话的时候，真正的意思是什么？
data.选项A: A. 考官在询问小李是否有考试压力。
data.选项B: B. 考官正在确认小李是否真的准备好开始测试。
data.选项C: C. 考官在提醒小李系好安全带后再启动发动机。
data.选项D: D. 考官在测试小李对重复问题的耐心。
data.STORY: Xiao Li is quite nervous when participating in the driver's road test, and wants to start the engine as soon as he gets in the car. The examiner asks next to him, "Are you ready!" Xiao Li says, "I am ready!" The examiner unbuckles his seat belt and buckles it again, and asks Xiao Li again, "Are you ready?"
data.QUESTION: What is the real meaning when the examiner says this?
data.OPTION-A: The examiner is asking if Xiao Li is under exam pressure.
data.OPTION-B: The examiner is confirming whether Xiao Li is really ready to start the test.
data.OPTION-C: The examiner is reminding Xiao Li to buckle up the seat belt before starting the engine.
data.OPTION-D: The examiner is testing Xiao Li's patience with repeated questions.

data.OPTION-B: The principal is reminding teachers to pay attention to improving teaching methods
data.OPTION-C: The principal pays attention to and cares about students' homework

data.故事: 19世纪，在奥地利的维也纳，妇女们喜欢戴一种高高耸起的帽子。她们进剧场看戏也不愿将帽子摘下，以致后排的观众被挡住了视线。经理上台请在座的女观众将帽子摘下来，然而说了半天妇女们也不予以理睬。最后经理又补充了一句：“那么，这样吧，年纪大一点的女士可以照顾，不必脱帽。”

data.选项C: C. 他对戴帽子的女士感到恼火。
data.选项D: D. 他在夸赞年纪大的女士的优雅。
data.STORY: In the 19th century, in Vienna, Austria, women like to wear a kind of towering hat. They go to the theater to watch plays and do not want to take off their hats, so the audience in the back row is blocked. The manager goes on stage to ask the female audience to take off their hats, but the women ignore him after a long talk. data.QUESTION: When the theater manager says these words, what does he really want to say?
data.OPTION-A: He hopes all ladies take off their hats.
data.OPTION-B: He only hopes young ladies take off their hats.
data.OPTION-C: He is annoyed with the ladies wearing hats.
data.OPTION-D: He is praising the elegance of older ladies.

data.故事: 李明是一个小学五年级的学生，最近喜欢上了一个流行的电子游戏。由于游戏太过迷人，他每天花费很多时间在这款游戏上。一天，妈妈对正在玩游戏的李明说：“你的游戏水平最近突飞猛进嘛。”
data.问题: 妈妈说这些话时，她真正想说的意思是什么？
data.选项A: A. 妈妈非常喜欢看李明玩游戏。
data.选项B: B. 妈妈想让李明教她怎么玩这款游戏。
data.选项C: C. 妈妈对李明游戏水平的提升感到欣喜。
data.选项D: D. 妈妈暗示李明最近花费太多时间在游戏上了。
data.STORY: Li Ming is a fifth-grade elementary school student who recently falls in love with a popular electronic game. Because the game is too captivating, he spends a lot of time on this game every day. One day, his mother says to Li Ming who is playing the game, "Your game level improves rapidly recently."
data.QUESTION: What does she really mean when she says these words?
data.OPTION-A: Mother really enjoys watching Li Ming play games.
data.OPTION-B: Mother wants Li Ming to teach her how to play this game.
data.OPTION-C: Mother feels happy about the improvement of Li Ming's game level.
data.OPTION-D: Mother hints that Li Ming spends too much time on the game recently.

data.故事: 妈妈正在厨房做晚饭，她打开冰箱，对正在客厅看电视的儿子李明说：“真糟糕，家里的鸡蛋没有了，我正要做西红柿炒鸡蛋来着。”

data.OPTION-B: Mom is complaining that Li Ming does not replenish the food in time.
data.OPTION-C: Mom hopes Li Ming goes to buy some eggs.
data.OPTION-D: Mom is hinting that she may need to change the dinner menu.

data.故事: 在办公室，小林在办公桌前苦苦研读手里的文件。他的同事小杨进来，看了一眼他的桌前满杯的咖啡，然后说：“小林，你的咖啡已经冷掉了。”
data.问题: 当小杨说这句话的时候，她真正想说的是什么？

data.OPTION-C: Xiao Yang questions the work efficiency of Xiao Lin.
data.OPTION-D: Xiao Yang hopes Xiao Lin drinks more water and less coffee.

data.故事: 小红是一个清洁工，她在办公楼的电梯里看到一位陌生男子正在吃瓜子，并将瓜子皮丢在地上。她面带微笑地对男子说：“先生，我们这里的垃圾桶在每层楼都有。”
data.问题: 当小红说这句话的时候，她真正想说的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 小红是在询问男子是否看到了垃圾桶。
data.选项B: B. 小红想告诉那个男子她的工作是清洁工。
data.选项C: C. 小红想告诉那个男子他应该把吃瓜子后的垃圾丢进垃圾桶。
data.选项D: D. 小红是在向男子介绍楼内垃圾桶的分布情况。
data.STORY: Xiao Hong is a cleaner, she sees a strange man eating sunflower seeds in the elevator of the office building, and he throws the seed shells on the ground. She smiles at the man and says, "Sir, we have trash cans on every floor here."
data.QUESTION: What does Xiao Hong really want to say when she says this?
data.OPTION-A: Xiao Hong is asking the man if he sees the trash can.
data.OPTION-B: Xiao Hong wants to tell the man that her job is a cleaner.
data.OPTION-C: Xiao Hong wants to tell the man that he should throw the trash from eating sunflower seeds into the trash can.
data.OPTION-D: Xiao Hong is introducing the distribution of trash cans in the building to the man.

data.问题: 当小华说这句话的时候，他真正想说的是什么？

data.选项D: D. 小华希望他和小雨购买一套专业的摄影设备。
data.STORY: Xiaoyu and Xiaohua are a couple. One day, Xiaoyu puts their IDs together, saying it is to see who looks better, Xiaohua says, "Doesn't the comparison require the same lighting, the same photographer, and the same conditions to reach a correct conclusion? data.OPTION-D: Xiaohua hopes that he and Xiaoyu buy a set of professional photography equipment.

data.故事: 公司会议室里开会，员工小李正打瞌睡，经理对他说：“小李，昨天工作到很晚吧，要注意休息。”

data.故事: 陈伟是一名广东的大学生。有一年，广东流传禽流感，而在大学学校外面的超市里，大的新奥尔良烤鸡五折出售，不到十元，陈伟兴奋的买了一只。结账时，他身后的阿姨问他：＂小伙子，你知道最近有什么新闻吗？＂
data.问题: 当阿姨说这句话时，她真正想说的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 阿姨想询问陈伟关于政治新闻的看法。
data.选项B: B. 阿姨在无意中闲聊，想了解最近的新鲜事
data.选项C: C. 阿姨暗示禽流感流行的时节购买烤鸡不安全。
data.选项D: D. 阿姨想指出新奥尔良烤鸡的价格太便宜了。
data.STORY: Chen Wei is a college student in Guangdong. When he checks out, the aunt behind him asks him: "Young man, do you know what the latest news is?"
data.QUESTION: What does the aunt really want to say when she says this?
data.OPTION-A: The aunt wants to ask Chen Wei about his views on political news.
data.OPTION-B: The aunt is casually chatting, wanting to know the latest happenings.
data.OPTION-C: The aunt implies that it is unsafe to buy roast chicken during the bird flu season.
data.OPTION-D: The aunt wants to point out that the price of New Orleans roast chicken is too cheap.

data.故事:
鸿杰去银行帮朋友办事，朋友在外地，他找到工作人员要来了办事需要填写的表单，看到了签名那栏，愣住了，因为显示要本人签字。
他很耿直的问工作人员：“我朋友在外地，我可以代签吗？”
工作人员说：“这里有监控，是没法别人代签的，出去找本人签。”
他很着急的说：“我朋友真的回不来，行个方便吧。”
工作人员还是那句话：“这里有监控，别人没法代签，出去找本人签。”
data.问题: 当工作人员说这句话时，他真正想说的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 工作人员是在硬性要求鸿杰必须找他的朋友来银行签字。
data.选项B: B. 工作人员在暗示鸿杰可以走出银行后帮朋友代签。
data.选项C: C. 工作人员是再次确认了规定，即银行内不允许他人代签。
data.选项D: D. 工作人员是在建议鸿杰去找合适的签字工具。
data.STORY:
Hongjie goes to the bank to help a friend with some business. His friend is out of town. He gets the form that needs to be filled out from the staff and stops when he sees the signature column because it requires the person's own signature.
He asks the staff very straightforwardly: "My friend is out of town, can I sign for him?"
The staff says: "There is surveillance here, it is impossible for others to sign on behalf, go find the person to sign."
He says anxiously: "My friend really can't come back, please make it convenient."
The staff still says: "There is surveillance here, others can't sign on behalf, go find the person to sign."
data.QUESTION: What does the staff really mean when he says this?
data.OPTION-A: The staff is insisting that Hongjie must find his friend to come to the bank to sign.
data.OPTION-B: The staff is hinting that Hongjie can sign for his friend after leaving the bank.
data.OPTION-C: The staff is reconfirming the rule that the bank does not allow others to sign on behalf.
data.OPTION-D: The staff is suggesting that Hongjie find a suitable signing tool.

data.故事: 跃生小时候晚上经常去一个年纪相仿的邻居家玩。某一天玩到深夜，他妈妈临进房间睡觉时，过来跟跃生说，“明天再来玩哈。”跃生觉得受到了邀请，本来第二天不太想找他玩的，为了不辜负这份好意，又勉为其难去他家玩到半夜。他妈妈临进房间睡觉时，又过来跟跃生说，“明天再来玩哈。”

data.选项C: C. 她暗示跃生应该离开了。
data.选项D: D. 她觉得跃生是个能给她儿子带来乐趣的朋友。
data.STORY: Yue Sheng often goes to a neighbor's house of the same age to play at night when he is a child. One day, he plays until late at night, his mother comes to him before going to bed and says, "Come to play again tomorrow." Yue Sheng feels invited, he doesn't really want to play with him the next day, but in order not to disappoint this kindness, he reluctantly goes to his house to play until midnight. His mother comes to him before going to bed and says, "Come to play again tomorrow."
data.QUESTION: What does the neighbor's mother really mean when she says this?
data.OPTION-A: She really likes Yue Sheng.
data.OPTION-B: She hopes Yue Sheng comes to her house to play every day.
data.OPTION-C: She hints that Yue Sheng should leave.
data.OPTION-D: She thinks Yue Sheng is a friend who brings fun to her son.

data.STORY: Xiaoxue is a capable and enthusiastic housewife. Old Pan is an old man who spends all day in the chess and card club, not caring about other things. One day, Xiaoxue passes by Old Pan's house, takes a look and says to Old Pan: "Uncle Pan, your garden is really a green paradise."

data.OPTION-D: Xiaoxue admires Old Pan's gardening skills.

data.故事: 经理小张在公司开会的时候，发现他的同事小赵一直玩手机。他看了一眼小赵并说着：“我发现你一直在研究一些非常重要的东西啊。”

data.STORY: Wang Yuan breaks up with his girlfriend for a year already. data.选项D: D. 班主任对李晨失望，不希望他再来上课

data.OPTION-C: The head teacher implies that Li Chen should attend class on time and not be late
data.OPTION-D: The head teacher is disappointed in Li Chen and does not want him to attend class anymore

data.选项A: A. 她觉得舞蹈服颜色不好看。
data.选项B: B. 她认为有人在偷偷穿社团的舞蹈服。
data.选项C: C. 她暗示舞蹈服已经旧了，需要购买新的。
data.选项D: D. 她对舞蹈社团的成员们抱怨太多。
data.STORY: Xiao Yang is the person in charge of the dance club. One day, she looks at the club's dance costumes and says, "These dance costumes make people feel heartbroken."
data.QUESTION: What does Xiao Yang really mean when she says this?
data.OPTION-A: She thinks the color of the dance costumes is not good.
data.OPTION-B: She believes someone secretly wears the club's dance costumes.
data.OPTION-C: She implies that the dance costumes are old and need to buy new ones.
data.OPTION-D: She complains too much about the members of the dance club.

data.故事: 小杨所在的公司周三有周例会。某周一，领导带着小王去会见客户张局，两人一直相谈甚欢，但谈的都是一些无关痛痒的话题，因为正事存在观点分歧。眼看着将近饭点，出现了下面几句对话： 领导：“张局，快到饭点了，看您有时间吗？想约您吃个饭？” 然后领导转过身，边眨眼睛，边对小杨说：“小杨，咱们晚上单位还有会议吗？”
data.问题: 当领导问小杨这个问题的时候，他的目的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 领导想向小杨询问会议时间，以安排和客户的饭局。
data.选项B: B. 领导希望小杨回答今晚有会议，以此借口结束会面。
data.选项C: C.领导想了解小杨对周例会的准备情况。
data.选项D: D. 领导希望询问小杨愿不愿不参加会议，而陪他们吃饭。
data.STORY: Xiao Yang's company holds a weekly meeting every Wednesday. On a certain Monday, the leader takes Xiao Wang to meet with client Director Zhang. The two of them chat happily, but they only talk about some irrelevant topics because there are disagreements on the main issues. As it approaches mealtime, the following conversation occurs: Leader: "Director Zhang, it is almost mealtime, do you have time? I want to invite you to have a meal." Then the leader turns around, winks, and says to Xiao Yang: "Xiao Yang, do we have a meeting at the unit tonight?"
data.QUESTION: What is the leader's purpose when he asks Xiao Yang this question?
data.OPTION-A: The leader wants to ask Xiao Yang about the meeting time to arrange a meal with the client.
data.OPTION-B: The leader hopes Xiao Yang answers that there is a meeting tonight, so he can use this as an excuse to end the meeting.
data.OPTION-C: The leader wants to understand Xiao Yang's preparation for the weekly meeting.
data.OPTION-D: The leader wants to ask if Xiao Yang is willing to skip the meeting and join them for dinner.

data.故事: 小汪和网络上认识的女生小兰的见面约在了酒店。在前台，小兰不愿意出示身份证登记。 前台工作人员问：“您是一位还是两位？两位的话需要出示双方身份证的先生。” 小汪回头看着小兰，她慢慢走到沙发边上坐下仍然没有出示身份证的意思。于是小汪转过头问：“两位，那怎么办？” 此时前台工作人员又问：“您是一位入住还是两位呢？”
data.问题: 当工作人员提出这个问题的时候，他的目的是什么？
data.选项A: A. 他没有听清楚小汪之前的回答，要再进行确认。
data.选项B: B. 他正在重新核实小汪的住宿需求。
data.选项C: C. 他暗示小汪可回答一位入住，这样只需要用一个人的身份证。
data.选项D: D. 他暗示不出示两人身份证就不可以一起住宿。
data.STORY: Xiao Wang and the girl he meets online, Xiao Lan, arrange to meet at a hotel. At the front desk, Xiao Lan does not want to show her ID for registration. The front desk staff asks, "Are you one or two? If two, the gentleman needs to show both IDs." Xiao Wang turns his head and looks at Xiao Lan, she slowly walks to the edge of the sofa and sits down, still showing no intention of showing her ID. So Xiao Wang turns his head and asks, "Two, what to do?" At this time, the front desk staff asks again, "Are you checking in for one or two?"
data.QUESTION: What is his purpose when the staff asks this question?
data.OPTION-A: He does not hear Xiao Wang's previous answer clearly and needs to confirm again.
data.OPTION-B: He is re-verifying Xiao Wang's accommodation needs.
data.OPTION-C: He hints that Xiao Wang can answer one person checks in, so only one person's ID is needed.
data.OPTION-D: He hints that if they do not show both IDs, they cannot stay together.

data.故事: 健身教练张佳丽有一次开车没带安全带被交警拍到了。交警走过来问张佳丽：“为什么没系安全带？是不是怀孕了？”
data.问题: 当交警问这个问题时，他真正的意图是什么？
data.选项A: A. 交警想要了解张佳丽的个人生活
data.选项B: B. 交警想确认张佳丽是否怀孕了，因为怀孕的人不用系安全带
data.选项C: C. 交警希望张佳丽去医院做孕检
data.选项D: D. 交警暗示张佳丽可以回答自己怀孕了，以避免罚款
data.STORY: Fitness coach Zhang Jiali drives without a seatbelt one time and a traffic cop catches her. The traffic cop comes over and asks Zhang Jiali, "Why don't you wear a seatbelt? Are you pregnant?"
data.QUESTION: What is the real intention of the traffic cop when he asks this question?
data.OPTION-A: The traffic cop wants to know about Zhang Jiali's personal life
data.OPTION-B: The traffic cop wants to confirm if Zhang Jiali is pregnant, because pregnant people do not need to wear seatbelts
data.OPTION-C: The traffic cop hopes Zhang Jiali goes to the hospital for a pregnancy test
data.OPTION-D: The traffic cop implies that Zhang Jiali can say she is pregnant to avoid a fine
